var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"category":"section","location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","text":"All exported macros and functions of Pinax.jl.","title":"API Reference"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.BibEntry","page":"API Reference","text":"A bibliography entry reduced to the fields the gallery renders.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.BibEntry"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.BuildContext","page":"API Reference","text":"Build state of the implicit global document (current page/section).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.BuildContext"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.Comment","page":"API Reference","text":"One comment turn: who wrote it and the markdown body.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.Comment"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.Desc","page":"API Reference","text":"Markdown + LaTeX source (unrendered; the theme draws it).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.Desc"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.DiagEntry","page":"API Reference","text":"One diagnostic. item is the anchor of the related page/section/figure.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.DiagEntry"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.Diagnostics","page":"API Reference","text":"error/warning entries collected during render (-> diagnostics page, notes 09).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.Diagnostics"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.DocMeta","page":"API Reference","text":"Document settings (analogous to TeX \\documentclass + preamble).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.DocMeta"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.Document","page":"API Reference","text":"Implicit top level (the catalogue). Order = tree position; numbers are not stored (numbering is the theme's job).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.Document"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.EmitCtx","page":"API Reference","text":"State threaded through the gallery emit functions for one render.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.EmitCtx"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.FigRef","page":"API Reference","text":"Lightweight handle pointing at a figure (used by thumbnails, etc.).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.FigRef"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.Figure","page":"API Reference","text":"A single figure (placeholder). gen is deferred; code is the expression source for change detection (notes 10).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.Figure"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.GalleryTheme","page":"API Reference","text":"Default theme: a self-contained HTML gallery (v1 minimal).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.GalleryTheme"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.Page","page":"API Reference","text":"A page (standalone HTML + shared nav).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.Page"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.RenderCache","page":"API Reference","text":"Per-render cache state: the previous manifest (read from disk) and the one being built. vault (if set) lets the cache key track the figure's DataVault data, not just its code+params.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.RenderCache"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.Section","page":"API Reference","text":"A section (a group of figures + a description).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.Section"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pinax.Severity","page":"API Reference","text":"Diagnostic severity (notes 09).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.Severity"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax._default_numberer-Tuple{Symbol, Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"Default numbering function: Sec. N / Fig. N / (N) for equations. Override it in the preamble with @pinaxsetup numberer = (kind, c) -> …, where kind is :section, :figure, or :equation and c is (; page, page_id, section, figure, subfigure, equation) — page is the 1-based page index and page_id its id (Symbol), so a numberer can prefix per \"part\" (e.g. c.page_id === :eq ? \"EQ$(c.section)\" : \"GQ$(c.section)\", usually with numbering=:page); section is the current section number, figure the document-wide figure count, subfigure the figure's index within its section (for hierarchical schemes like Fig. 2.3), and equation the document-wide equation count.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax._default_numberer"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax._finalize_cache!-Tuple{Pinax.RenderCache}","page":"API Reference","text":"Write the new manifest and delete asset files the previous render produced but this one did not.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax._finalize_cache!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax._materialize-Tuple{Pinax.Figure, Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"_materialize(fig, base, fmts) -> Vector{String}\n\nCall the deferred fig.gen exactly once to produce the figure, write the assets, and return their paths (notes 02 pass 3). Figure objects are saved per fmt via pinax_save; an existing file path is copied (the file must exist when gen() returns).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax._materialize"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax._resolve_theme-Tuple{Theme}","page":"API Reference","text":"_resolve_theme(spec) -> Theme\n\nResolve a theme spec to a Theme: a Theme instance is returned as-is; a Symbol is looked up in the registry; an AbstractString is treated as a path to a .jl file that must evaluate to a Theme.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax._resolve_theme"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax._save_with-NTuple{4, Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"_save_with(saver, obj, base, fmt) -> path\n\nHelper for backend extensions. Builds the destination path base.<fmt>, ensures its directory exists, runs saver(obj, dest) — the contract is (obj, dest): figure first, path second — verifies a file was actually written, and returns it.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax._save_with"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax.add_comment-Tuple{AbstractString, Any, AbstractString}","page":"API Reference","text":"add_comment(path, id, text; author=\"\") -> path\n\nAppend one comment turn for id to the TOML at path (created if absent), preserving existing turns and bookmarks. This is the CLI / LLM-loop write path: julia -e 'using Pinax; Pinax.add_comment(\"comments.toml\", :eq_energy, \"…\"; author=\"llm\")'.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.add_comment"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax.document-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"Build a scoped document: doc = document() do … end (for test isolation).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.document"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax.emit_document-Tuple{GalleryTheme, Pinax.Document, AbstractString, Pinax.RenderCache}","page":"API Reference","text":"Emit the doc tree to a single HTML file. Doubles as pass 3 (materialize + draw) (notes 02/06).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.emit_document"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax.emit_document-Tuple{Theme, Any, Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"emit_document(theme, doc, outdir, cache; comments_file) -> path\n\nRender doc into outdir and return the entry-file path. This is the one method every theme must implement; render dispatches here on the resolved theme.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.emit_document"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax.is_figure-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"Is x a backend figure object? Defaults to false (Plots/Makie ext overrides).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.is_figure"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax.materialize!-Tuple{Pinax.Figure, Any, Any, Pinax.RenderCache}","page":"API Reference","text":"materialize!(fig, base, fmts, cache) -> :hit | :miss\n\nPopulate fig.assets. On a cache hit (unchanged key + assets still present) the deferred gen is NOT called. On a miss, materialize for real and record the result in the new manifest. May rethrow whatever _materialize throws (the caller turns it into a diagnostic).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.materialize!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax.pinax_save-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"pinax_save(x, base, fmt) -> path\n\nSave the figure object x to base (an extensionless base path) in fmt (:svg/:pdf/…) and return the actual path. Per-backend implementations are injected via package extensions (weakdeps) (notes 04).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.pinax_save"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax.read_comments-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API Reference","text":"read_comments(path) -> (comments, bookmarks)\n\nRead an id-keyed comments TOML. Returns comments::Dict{Symbol,Vector{Comment}} (id -> turns, in file order) and bookmarks::Set{Symbol}. A missing or unparseable file yields empties (non-fatal).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.read_comments"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax.register_theme!-Tuple{Symbol, Theme}","page":"API Reference","text":"Register theme under name so it can be selected with @pinaxsetup theme=name / render(theme=name).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.register_theme!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Pinax.render","page":"API Reference","text":"render([doc]; out, theme=GalleryTheme(), force=false) -> path\n\nRender the catalogue: structure (pass 1, done by macros) -> resolve (pass 2) -> materialize + emit (pass 3, theme). Writes into the out directory and returns the path of the generated entry file. doc defaults to the implicit global document. force=true re-materializes every figure, ignoring the cache (notes 10).\n\ncomments_file is the id-keyed annotation store read and shown inline by the gallery (default out/comments.toml). render only READS it — it persists across renders and is written by the CLI / browser export / LLM loop, never overwritten here.\n\ntheme selects the renderer: a Theme instance, a registered Symbol, or a path to a user theme file (see theme.jl). nothing (default) uses the document's @pinaxsetup theme=….\n\nvault is an optional DataVault.Vault (notes 05): when given, (1) the cache key tracks each params::DataKey figure's data via its .done marker, so recomputing the data re-materializes the figure (not just code/param changes), and (2) figure provenance is recorded with DataVault.record_figure under study (defaults to the vault's run).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.render"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax.reset!-Tuple{}","page":"API Reference","text":"Reset the implicit document (fresh, empty). The preamble @pinaxsetup calls this.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.reset!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax.resolve!-Tuple{Pinax.Document}","page":"API Reference","text":"resolve!(doc) -> doc\n\npass 2 (structure only, no numbers). Builds the label->node table. Numbers are assigned by the theme (CSS), so none are emitted here. Facet expansion and full diagnostic collection come in later slices.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.resolve!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pinax.resolved_thumbnail-Tuple{Pinax.Page}","page":"API Reference","text":"Resolve a page's main figure: explicit @thumbnail > thumbnail=true marker > top (first) figure (notes 02).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.resolved_thumbnail"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Pinax.serve","page":"API Reference","text":"serve(dir=\"out\"; host=\"localhost\", port=8000, blocking=true) -> nothing | handle\n\nServe the rendered gallery in dir over HTTP so you can open the printed link in a browser. Picks the next free port from port if it is busy. Blocks until interrupted (Ctrl-C); with blocking=false it returns (; server, url, port, task) and you close(handle.server) to stop.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.serve"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Pinax.set_bookmark!","page":"API Reference","text":"set_bookmark!(path, id, on=true) -> path\n\nMark/unmark id as bookmarked in the TOML at path.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.set_bookmark!"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@bibliography-Tuple","page":"API Reference","text":"Declare the .bib source(s) used to resolve @cite. @bibliography \"refs/a.bib\" …\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@bibliography"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@caption-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"Attach a caption to the preceding @figure (like \\caption); it overwrites any caption= set there, since it runs afterward.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@caption"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@debug_mode-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"Diagnostics mode. @debug_mode true\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@debug_mode"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@desc-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"Section description (markdown + LaTeX source). @desc md\"…\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@desc"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@figure-Tuple","page":"API Reference","text":"Register a plot; the expression is DEFERRED. @figure expr [params=…] [caption=…] [id=…] [thumbnail=…] / @figure [kw] begin … end\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@figure"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@md_str-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"Raw string (preserves $…$). Used by @desc md\"…\" etc.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@md_str"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@newcommand-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"Notation macro. @newcommand \"\\E\" raw\"\\langle H\\rangle\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@newcommand"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@no_thumbnail-Tuple{}","page":"API Reference","text":"This page contributes no main figure to the index.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@no_thumbnail"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@page-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"A page. @page :id \"Title\" begin … end\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@page"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@pinaxsetup-Tuple","page":"API Reference","text":"Document settings + reset of the implicit document. @pinaxsetup theme=… index=… numbering=… debug=…\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@pinaxsetup"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@raw-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"Inject a raw block into the current section — the escape hatch for project-specific UI that markdown can't express (coverage tables, broken-data banners; notes 06 §6). @raw x evaluates x to a string and the theme emits it verbatim (the gallery as raw HTML; trusted author content): @raw raw\"<table class=cov>…</table>\". Use @desc for prose; @raw for hand-built markup.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@raw"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@section-Tuple","page":"API Reference","text":"A section. @section :id \"Title\" [by=…] [summary=…] [layout=…] begin … end\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@section"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#Pinax.@thumbnail-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","text":"Set the page main figure. @thumbnail :figid (priority: explicit @thumbnail > a thumbnail=true @figure > the top figure; notes 02 resolve).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pinax.@thumbnail"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/lsystems/#Example-2-·-L-system-fractals","page":"L-system fractals","text":"← All examples\n\nSource: LSystems.jl — DEFINED_LSYSTEMS, grow_string, LSystems.string2positions.\n\n<p style=\"margin:.2rem 0 1rem\"><a href=\"../galleries/lsystems/\"><b>▶ Open the compiled Pinax gallery</b></a></p>\n\nAn L-system grows a string by repeatedly applying substitution rules to an axiom, then a turtle interprets the string as geometry. LSystems.jl loads each system from a JSON config; we grow it a few iterations and turn it into a polyline with string2positions.\n\nusing Pinax, LSystems, Plots\n\n# grow an L-system `iter` times and draw the turtle path (NaN gaps = branch returns)\nfunction lsys(name, iter; kw...)\n    tile = DEFINED_LSYSTEMS[name]\n    pos  = LSystems.string2positions(tile, grow_string(tile, iter))\n    xs = [p[1] for p in pos]\n    ys = [p[2] for p in pos]\n    plot(xs, ys; legend=false, aspect_ratio=:equal, axis=false, ticks=false,\n         grid=false, lw=0.6, size=(380, 380), kw...)\nend\nnothing # hide\n\nPinax.reset!(; title = \"L-system fractals (Pinax demo)\")\n\n@page :fractals \"L-system fractals\" begin\n    @section :koch \"Koch & Sierpiński\" begin\n        @desc md\"\"\"\n        Boundary fractals from simple edge-replacement rules. The Koch curve has Hausdorff\n        dimension $D=\\log 4/\\log 3\\approx1.26$; the Sierpiński gasket, $D=\\log 3/\\log 2\\approx1.58$.\n        \"\"\"\n        @figure lsys(\"kochcurve\", 4; title=\"Koch curve\", lc=:steelblue)\n        @caption \"Koch curve (4 iterations)\"\n        @figure lsys(\"kocksnowflake\", 4; title=\"Koch snowflake\", lc=:steelblue)\n        @caption \"Koch snowflake (4 iterations)\"\n        @figure lsys(\"sierpinskigasket\", 6; title=\"Sierpiński gasket\", lc=:seagreen)\n        @caption \"Sierpiński gasket (6 iterations)\"\n    end\n    @section :curves \"Dragons, space-filling & plants\" begin\n        @desc md\"\"\"\n        A self-similar dragon, a space-filling curve that visits every cell of a grid as the\n        iteration count grows, and a bracketed system whose $[\\,\\ldots\\,]$ push/pop the turtle\n        state to make a branching plant.\n        \"\"\"\n        @figure lsys(\"heighwaydragon\", 11; title=\"Heighway dragon\", lc=:firebrick)\n        @caption \"Heighway dragon (11 iterations)\"\n        @figure lsys(\"hilbeltpath\", 5; title=\"Hilbert curve\", lc=:darkorange)\n        @caption \"Hilbert space-filling curve (5 iterations)\"\n        @figure lsys(\"ternarybranching\", 6; title=\"Ternary branching\", lc=:seagreen)\n        @caption \"Ternary branching plant (6 iterations)\"\n    end\nend\n\nPinax.render(; out = \"galleries/lsystems\")\nnothing # hide\n\nA preview of the Hilbert curve, shown inline by Documenter:\n\nlsys(\"hilbeltpath\", 5; title=\"Hilbert curve\", lc=:darkorange)\n\n<p style=\"margin:1rem 0\"><a href=\"../galleries/lsystems/\"><b>▶ Open the rendered gallery</b></a></p>","title":"Example 2 · L-system fractals"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/#Examples","page":"Introduction","text":"This section is a small catalogue of galleries built with Pinax. It governs the example pages that follow: each one runs a real computation and then follows the same Pinax workflow —\n\ncompute something (integrate an ODE, grow an L-system, run a Monte Carlo sweep),\ndescribe a manuscript with @page / @section / @figure / @desc,\nrender it into a self-contained gallery you can open and share.\n\nSo the example pages double as copy-paste templates: read one for the source and the walkthrough, then open its compiled gallery to see what Pinax produces.","title":"Examples"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/#The-galleries","page":"Introduction","text":"","title":"The galleries"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/#1-·-Chaotic-attractors","page":"Introduction","text":"Lorenz & Rössler as 3-D attractors plus 2-D projections — a multi-section gallery with KaTeX math. Source & walkthrough.\n\n<p style=\"margin:.2rem 0 1.4rem\"><a href=\"galleries/attractors/\"><b>▶ Open the compiled gallery</b></a></p>","title":"1 · Chaotic attractors"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/#2-·-L-system-fractals","page":"Introduction","text":"Koch, Sierpiński, the Heighway dragon, a Hilbert space-filling curve and a branching plant, grown by substitution and drawn by turtle geometry. Source & walkthrough.\n\n<p style=\"margin:.2rem 0 1.4rem\"><a href=\"galleries/lsystems/\"><b>▶ Open the compiled gallery</b></a></p>","title":"2 · L-system fractals"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/#3-·-Ising-model-(Monte-Carlo)","page":"Introduction","text":"A 2-D Metropolis simulation: spin snapshots across the transition plus the magnetization curve. Source & walkthrough.\n\n<p style=\"margin:.2rem 0 1.4rem\"><a href=\"galleries/ising/\"><b>▶ Open the compiled gallery</b></a></p>","title":"3 · Ising model (Monte Carlo)"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/ising/#Example-3-·-Ising-model-(Monte-Carlo)","page":"Ising model (Monte Carlo)","text":"← All examples\n\nSource: self-contained — a 2-D Metropolis simulation written inline with Plots + Random.\n\n<p style=\"margin:.2rem 0 1rem\"><a href=\"../galleries/ising/\"><b>▶ Open the compiled Pinax gallery</b></a></p>\n\nA self-contained 2-D Ising Monte Carlo: Metropolis single-spin flips on a periodic lattice with Hamiltonian H=-Jsum_langle ijrangle s_i s_j, accepting a flip with probability minbigl(1 e^-betaDelta Ebigr). The model orders below the Onsager temperature T_c=2ln(1+sqrt 2)approx 2269 and disorders above it. No external dependencies — just Plots and Random.\n\nusing Pinax, Plots, Random\n\n# one Metropolis sweep (L*L attempted single-spin flips) at inverse temperature β\nfunction sweep!(s, β)\n    L = size(s, 1)\n    @inbounds for _ in 1:L*L\n        i = rand(1:L); j = rand(1:L)\n        nb = s[mod1(i-1, L), j] + s[mod1(i+1, L), j] + s[i, mod1(j-1, L)] + s[i, mod1(j+1, L)]\n        dE = 2 * s[i, j] * nb\n        (dE <= 0 || rand() < exp(-β * dE)) && (s[i, j] = -s[i, j])\n    end\n    return s\nend\n\n# run at temperature T; return the final configuration and the mean |magnetization|\nfunction run_ising(L, T; equil, measure)\n    s = rand((Int8(-1), Int8(1)), L, L)\n    β = 1 / T\n    for _ in 1:equil; sweep!(s, β); end\n    m = 0.0\n    for _ in 1:measure; sweep!(s, β); m += abs(sum(Int, s)) / (L * L); end\n    return s, m / measure\nend\n\nRandom.seed!(20240620)\nsnap(T) = heatmap(run_ising(64, T; equil=600, measure=1)[1]; aspect_ratio=:equal, c=:grays,\n                  axis=false, ticks=false, colorbar=false, size=(360, 360), title=\"T = $T\")\nnothing # hide\n\nTc = 2 / log(1 + sqrt(2))\n\nPinax.reset!(; title = \"2-D Ising model — Monte Carlo (Pinax demo)\")\n\n@page :ising \"Ising model (Monte Carlo)\" begin\n    @section :snapshots \"Spin configurations\" begin\n        @desc md\"\"\"\n        Equilibrated $64\\times64$ configurations (black/white = down/up spins) across the\n        transition $T_c\\approx2.269$: ordered, critical (large fluctuating clusters), disordered.\n        \"\"\"\n        @figure snap(1.5)\n        @caption md\"$T=1.5<T_c$ — ordered\"\n        @figure snap(2.27)\n        @caption md\"$T\\approx T_c$ — critical\"\n        @figure snap(3.5)\n        @caption md\"$T=3.5>T_c$ — disordered\"\n    end\n    @section :magnetization \"Magnetization curve\" begin\n        @desc md\"\"\"\n        Order parameter $\\langle\\lvert m\\rvert\\rangle(T)$ over a temperature sweep, with the Onsager\n        $T_c$ marked. It falls from $\\approx1$ (ordered) toward $0$ (disordered) near $T_c$.\n        \"\"\"\n        @figure begin\n            Ts = collect(1.0:0.2:3.6)\n            Ms = [run_ising(40, T; equil=400, measure=500)[2] for T in Ts]\n            plot(Ts, Ms; marker=:circle, lw=1.5, legend=:topright, label=\"⟨|m|⟩\",\n                 xlabel=\"T\", ylabel=\"⟨|m|⟩\", size=(560, 380))\n            vline!([Tc]; ls=:dash, lc=:red, label=\"Tc ≈ 2.269\")\n        end\n        @caption md\"$\\langle\\lvert m\\rvert\\rangle$ vs $T$ (40×40 lattice)\"\n    end\nend\n\nPinax.render(; out = \"galleries/ising\")\nnothing # hide\n\nA preview of a critical-temperature snapshot, shown inline by Documenter:\n\nsnap(2.27)\n\n<p style=\"margin:1rem 0\"><a href=\"../galleries/ising/\"><b>▶ Open the rendered gallery</b></a></p>","title":"Example 3 · Ising model (Monte Carlo)"},{"category":"section","location":"#Pinax.jl","page":"Home","text":"A board of figures that is also a catalogue.\n\nPinax turns the figures your analysis scripts produce into a structured, self-contained HTML gallery — sections as cards, a multi-column figure grid, markdown + math descriptions, cross-references, citations, and an interactive comment layer — and can export the same manuscript to PDF via a LaTeX theme.\n\nIt generalizes the hand-written build_report page that an analysis pipeline grows over time: you describe the manuscript once with a small DSL, point each figure at the value (or data key) it plots, and render writes the gallery.","title":"Pinax.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#The-shape-of-it","page":"Home","text":"using Pinax\n\n@page :results \"Results\" begin\n    @section :energy \"Energy\" begin\n        @desc md\"Energy density $E/N$ versus inverse temperature $\\beta$.\"\n        @figure plot_energy()          # any Plots/Makie figure — deferred until render\n        @caption \"χ-convergence\"\n    end\nend\n\nrender(out = \"site\")                    # -> site/index.html  (self-contained)\n# render(theme = :latex, out = \"pdf\")   # -> pdf/document.tex -> PDF\n\n@figure captures its expression lazily, so figures are only computed (and cached) when you render. Sections become cards; figures lay out in a responsive grid; $…$ math is rendered by KaTeX; serve(\"site\") previews it over HTTP.","title":"The shape of it"},{"category":"section","location":"#Where-to-go-next","page":"Home","text":"Examples — the index of worked-example galleries. Each is built live as a Documenter @example and rendered into a self-contained Pinax gallery you can open.\nAPI Reference — every exported macro and function.","title":"Where to go next"},{"category":"section","location":"examples/attractors/#Example-1-·-Chaotic-attractors","page":"Chaotic attractors","text":"← All examples\n\nSource: DynamicalModels.jl — Lorenz, Rossler, ode_solver(RK4, …).\n\n<p style=\"margin:.2rem 0 1rem\"><a href=\"../galleries/attractors/\"><b>▶ Open the compiled Pinax gallery</b></a></p>\n\nIntegrate the Lorenz and Rössler systems from DynamicalModels.jl and draw each as a 3-D attractor plus 2-D projections — three figures per section, so they lay out as a 3-column grid inside each section card.\n\nusing Pinax, DynamicalModels, Plots\n\n# integrate two chaotic attractors (DynamicalModels.jl: model(t, x) -> dx/dt, RK4 solver)\nt = collect(0.0:0.02:80.0)\nlorenz  = ode_solver(RK4, Lorenz(),  t, [1.0, 1.0, 1.0])\nrossler = ode_solver(RK4, Rossler(), t, [1.0, 1.0, 1.0])\n\n# plot helpers: a 3-D trajectory and a 2-D coordinate projection\norbit3d(tr; kw...) = plot(tr[:, 1], tr[:, 2], tr[:, 3]; legend=false, lw=0.4, size=(420, 360), kw...)\nproj(tr, i, j; kw...) = plot(tr[:, i], tr[:, j]; legend=false, lw=0.4, size=(420, 360), kw...)\nnothing # hide\n\nPinax.reset!(; title = \"Chaotic attractors — Lorenz & Rössler (Pinax demo)\")\n\n@page :attractors \"Chaotic attractors\" begin\n    @section :lorenz \"Lorenz\" begin\n        @desc md\"\"\"\n        The **Lorenz** system $\\dot x=\\sigma(y-x),\\ \\dot y=x(\\rho-z)-y,\\ \\dot z=xy-\\beta z$\n        with $\\sigma=10,\\ \\rho=28,\\ \\beta=8/3$ — the classic butterfly attractor.\n        \"\"\"\n        @figure orbit3d(lorenz; xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\", zlabel=\"z\", title=\"Lorenz 3-D\")\n        @caption md\"3-D attractor\"\n        @figure proj(lorenz, 1, 3; xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"z\", title=\"x–z\")\n        @caption md\"$x$–$z$ projection\"\n        @figure proj(lorenz, 1, 2; xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\", title=\"x–y\")\n        @caption md\"$x$–$y$ projection\"\n    end\n    @section :rossler \"Rössler\" begin\n        @desc md\"\"\"\n        The **Rössler** system $\\dot x=-y-z,\\ \\dot y=x+ay,\\ \\dot z=b+z(x-c)$\n        with $a=b=0.2,\\ c=5.7$.\n        \"\"\"\n        @figure orbit3d(rossler; xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\", zlabel=\"z\", title=\"Rössler 3-D\")\n        @caption md\"3-D attractor\"\n        @figure proj(rossler, 1, 2; xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\", title=\"x–y\")\n        @caption md\"$x$–$y$ projection\"\n        @figure proj(rossler, 2, 3; xlabel=\"y\", ylabel=\"z\", title=\"y–z\")\n        @caption md\"$y$–$z$ projection\"\n    end\nend\n\nPinax.render(; out = \"galleries/attractors\")\nnothing # hide\n\nA preview of the Lorenz attractor, shown inline by Documenter:\n\norbit3d(lorenz; xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\", zlabel=\"z\", title=\"Lorenz attractor\")\n\n<p style=\"margin:1rem 0\"><a href=\"../galleries/attractors/\"><b>▶ Open the rendered gallery</b></a></p>","title":"Example 1 · Chaotic attractors"}]
}
